Class StringIdentityMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<Object,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,HadoopIdentityKey>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableIdentityMapper<String>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EventIdentityMapper

    public abstract class StringIdentityMapper
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<Object,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,HadoopIdentityKey>
implements TableIdentityMapper<String>
    Definition of a map job that operates over records with a String typed main identifier. The majority of the work for this map job is performed by IdentityMapper; this class exists to satisfy the requirements of Hadoop that mappers statically declare their key type in terms of Hadoop-specific wrapper types.
